Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_add_target_pg_mode(25.10)                    get_add_target_pg_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_add_target_pg_mode  - Returns the information for the specified pa-
       rameter

Syntax
       get_add_target_pg_mode

       [-help]

        [-allow_weak_connect]

       [-max_extension_distance]

        [-pins]

        [-pins_group_distance]

        [-respect_routes]

        [-share_resource]

        [-quiet]

        [-nonDefault]

       Returns the information for the specified parameter. Note that you  can
       specify one or more parameter. When you invoke this command without any
       argument, the software prints the current values stored in the database
       for all the options. If you provide an option, then the software prints
       the value currently stored in the database.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each get_add_target_pg_mode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_add_target_pg_mode

       -parameter_names
              Returns  the information about the specified parameters. You can
              specify one or more parameters. See  set_add_target_pg_mode  for
              the description of the get_add_target_pg_mode parameters.

       -quiet Returns  the  current settings for the specified parameters only
              in the Tcl list format. If you specify -quiet without any  para-
              meters,  the  software  returns  the current settings of all the
              set_add_target_pg_mode parameters in Tcl list format.

Related Information
